title: Sidewall, 1845–55
creditline: Gift of Eleanor and Sarah Hewitt
description: Nearly a full repeat of a design showing a pair of birds perched on branches amidst dense foliage. Below the pair is a nest containing two eggs. The selvedge has been trimmed on the right side.

tombstone.epitaph:
Sidewall, 1845–55.
1845–55. Block-printed on paper. Gift of Eleanor and Sarah Hewitt. 1928-2-111.
